-- Consortium offered $24.5 bln for ABN AMRO's LaSalle
-- 
-- Mon May 14, 2007 4:29am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/05/14/us-abnamro-fortis-idUSBRE00097520070514

 

 BRUSSELS  (Reuters) - The consortium of banks seeking to take over ABN AMRO AAH.AS confirmed on Monday they offered $24.5 billion for the Dutch bank's U.S. unit LaSalle but their bid was rejected on May 6. 

 Royal Bank of Scotland ( RBS.L ), Spain's Santander ( SAN.MC ) and Belgian-Dutch Fortis FOR.BRFOR.AS, which seek to take over ABN AMRO, said they would make a further announcement by May 27.